definition.value: An androstanoid that is androsta-1,4,6-triene substituted by oxo groups at positions 3 and 17.

A mixture of intertwined and flexible glass fibres and a binder that sticks the fibres together to give a wool-like texture. Produced in rolls or slabs, it is used for thermal and acoustic insulation.
A monoalkyl phosphate that is ethyl phosphate in which one of the methyl hydrogens has been replaced by an isothiocyanato group.
A member of the class of dioxolanes that is 1,3-dioxolane substituted at position 2 by a 4-bromo-6,6,6-trichloro-2-methyl-2-hexanyl group.
A monocarboxylic acid that is thyroacetic acid carrying four iodo substituents at positions 3, 3', 5 and 5'.
A ketimine consisting of hexane carrying five hydroxy substituents at positions 1, 2, 3, 4 and 6 as well as the imino group at position 5.

A member of the class of pyrazoles that is N-[4-(pyrazol-1-yl)phenyl]glycinamide in which the pyrazole ring is substituted at positions 3 and 5 by trifluoromethyl and phenanthrene-2-yl groups respectively.
A member of the class of dioxolanes that is 1,3-dioxolane substituted at position 2 by a 2-(2-methoxyethoxy)ethoxy group.
A diol that is ethene substituted at positions 1 and 2 by hydroxy groups (the Z-geoisomer).
A 3-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is butyric acid substituted at positions 2 and 3 by ethyl and oxo groups respectively.
